{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"PHP","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Philippians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Philippians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Philippians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Philippians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Philippians"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Greetings from Paul and Timothy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../colossians/1.htm|>Colossians 1:1–2</a>; <a href =|../philemon/1.htm|>Philemon 1:1–3</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Paul and Timothy, servants of Christ Jesus, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["To all the saints in Christ Jesus   at Philippi, together with the overseers and deacons: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Thanksgiving and Prayer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../1_corinthians/1.htm#4|>1 Corinthians 1:4–9</a>; <a href =|../colossians/1.htm#3|>Colossians 1:3–14</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"I thank my  God   every time I remember you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"In every prayer for all of you, I always   pray with joy, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"because of your  partnership in the gospel from the first day until  now, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"being confident of this , that He who began a good work in you will carry it on to completion until the day of Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}," It is right for me to feel this way about all of you, since I  have you in my heart. For in  my  chains and in my defense and confirmation of the gospel, you are all partners in grace with me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"  God is my witness how I long for all of you with the affection of Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And this is my prayer: that your  love may abound  more and more in knowledge and depth of insight, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"so that you  may be able to test and prove what is best and may be pure and blameless for the day of Christ, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"filled with the fruit of righteousness that comes through Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Paul’s Trials Advance the Gospel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../james/1.htm#2|>James 1:2–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Now I want you to know, brothers, that my circumstances   have actually served to advance the gospel. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"As a result, it has become clear throughout the whole palace guard ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>all the Praetorium</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and to everyone else that I am  in chains for Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And  most of the brothers, confident in the Lord by my chains, now dare more greatly to speak the word ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>the word of God</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"without fear. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"It is true that some preach  Christ  out of envy and rivalry, but others  out of goodwill. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The latter do so in love, knowing that I am appointed for the defense of the gospel. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR reverse the order of verses 16 and 17."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"The former, however, preach  Christ out of selfish ambition, not sincerely, supposing that they can add to the distress of my  chains. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"What then  is the issue ? ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>What then?</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"Just this: that in every way, whether by false motives or true, Christ is preached. And in this I rejoice. Yes, and I will continue to rejoice, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"because I know that through your  prayers and the provision of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,  my distress  will turn out for my  deliverance. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," I  eagerly expect and hope that I will in no way be ashamed  , but   will have complete boldness so that now as always Christ will be exalted in my  body, whether by life or by death. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>To Live Is Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For to me,  to live is Christ, and  to die is gain. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But if  I go on living in the body, this will mean fruitful labor for me. So what shall I choose?  I do not know. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," I am torn between the two.   I desire   to depart and be with Christ, which is far  better indeed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"But  it is more necessary for you that I remain in the body. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," Convinced of this, I know that I will remain and will continue with all of you for your  progress and joy in the faith, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"so that through my  coming to you again  your exultation in Christ Jesus will resound on account of me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Worthy of the Gospel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Nevertheless, conduct yourselves in a manner worthy of the gospel  of Christ. Then, whether I come and see you or only hear  about you in my absence, I will know that you stand firm in one spirit, contending together as one  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>striving together with one mind</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"for the faith of the gospel, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"}," without being frightened  in any way by those who oppose you. This is a clear sign of their destruction but of your salvation, and it is from God. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"For it has been granted to you  on behalf of Christ not only  to believe in Him, but also  to suffer for Him, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"since you are encountering the same struggle  you saw  I had, and now hear that  I still have . "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>One in Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../ephesians/2.htm#11|>Ephesians 2:11–18</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Therefore if you have any encouragement in Christ, if any comfort from His love, if any fellowship with the Spirit, if any affection and compassion, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"then make my  joy complete    by being like-minded, having the same love, being united in spirit and   purpose. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Do nothing out of selfish ambition or  empty pride, but  in humility consider others more important than yourselves. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Each of you should look not only to your own interests, but  also to the interests of others. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Mind of Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/52.htm#13|>Isaiah 52:13–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Let this mind be  in you which was also in Christ Jesus: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Who, existing in the form of God, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["did not consider   equality with God "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["something to be grasped, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>something to be exploited</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"but emptied Himself, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["taking the form of a servant, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["being made in human likeness . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And being found in appearance as a man, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He humbled Himself "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and became obedient to death —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even death on a cross. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Therefore   God exalted Him to the highest place "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and gave Him the name above all  names, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in heaven and on earth and under the earth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to the glory of God the Father. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Lights in the World"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../matthew/5.htm#13|>Matthew 5:13–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Therefore, my beloved, just as  you have always obeyed, not only  in my  presence, but now even more in my  absence, continue to work out your  salvation with fear and trembling. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"For it is God who works in you   to will and  to act on behalf of His good purpose. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Do everything without complaining or arguing, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"so that you may be blameless and pure, children of God without fault in a crooked and perverse generation, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Deuteronomy 32:5"]}],"caller":"+"},"in which you shine as lights in the world ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"as you hold forth the word of life, in order that I may boast on the day of Christ that  I did not run   or labor in vain. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But even if I am being poured out like a drink offering on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I am glad and rejoice with all of you. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"  So you too should be glad and rejoice with me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Timothy and Epaphroditus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../1_corinthians/16.htm#10|>1 Corinthians 16:10–12</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Now I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon, that I also may be cheered when I learn  how you are doing. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," I have nobody else like him who will genuinely care for your needs . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For all the others look after their own interests, not those of Jesus Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But you know Timothy’s  proven worth, that as a child with his father he has served with me to advance the gospel. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"So  I hope to send him as soon as   I see what happens with me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"And I trust in the Lord that I myself  will come soon. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But I thought it necessary to send back to you Epaphroditus, my  brother,  fellow worker, and fellow soldier, who is also your messenger and minister to my  needs. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"For he has been longing for all of you and is distressed because you heard  he was ill. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," He was sick indeed, nearly unto death. But  God had mercy on him, and not only on him but also on me, to  spare me sorrow upon sorrow. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Therefore I am all the more eager to send him, so that when you see him again you may rejoice, and I may be less anxious. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," Welcome him in the Lord with great joy, and  honor  men like him, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"because he nearly  died for the work of Christ, risking his life  to make up for your  deficit of service to me. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Righteousness through Faith in Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../romans/3.htm#21|>Romans 3:21–31</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord. It is no trouble for me to write the same things to you again, and it is a safeguard for you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Watch out for those dogs,  those workers of evil,  those mutilators of the flesh! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For it is we who are the circumcision, we who worship by the Spirit of God, who glory in Christ Jesus, and who  put no confidence in the flesh —  ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"though I myself  could have such confidence  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["If anyone else thinks he has grounds for confidence in the flesh, I have more: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"circumcised on the eighth day, of the people of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin; a Hebrew of Hebrews; as to the law, a Pharisee; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"as to zeal, persecuting the church; as to righteousness  in the law,  faultless. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"But whatever was gain to me  I count as loss for the sake of  Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"More than that    , I count all things as loss compared to the surpassing excellence of knowing Christ Jesus my  Lord, for whom I have lost  all things.  I consider them rubbish, that I may gain Christ ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"and be found in Him, not having my own righteousness  from the law, but that which is through faith in Christ, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>through the faithfulness of Christ</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"the righteousness from God on the basis of  faith. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," I want to know Christ and the power of His resurrection and the fellowship of His sufferings, being conformed to Him in His death, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and so, somehow, to attain to the resurrection  from the dead. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Pressing on toward the Goal"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Not that  I have already obtained all this, or  have already been made perfect, but I press on   to take hold of that for which   Christ Jesus  took hold of me. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Brothers, I do not consider myself yet to have taken hold of it. But one thing I do : Forgetting what is behind and straining toward what is ahead, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I press on toward the goal to win the prize of  God’s heavenly calling in Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"}," All of us who are mature  should embrace this point of view. And if you think differently about some issue,  God will reveal this to you as well. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Nevertheless, we must live up   to what we have already attained. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Citizenship in Heaven"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Join one another in following  my example, brothers, and carefully observe those who  walk according to the pattern we set for you . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For as I have often told  you before, and now say again even with tears: Many live  as enemies of the cross  of Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Their  end is destruction, their  god is their belly, and their glory is in their  shame. Their minds are set on earthly things. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But our  citizenship is in heaven, and we eagerly await a Savior from there, the Lord Jesus Christ, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"who, by the power   that enables Him  to subject  all things to Himself, will transform our  lowly  bodies to be like  His  glorious body. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Rejoice in the Lord"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Therefore, my brothers, whom I love and long for, my joy and crown, that is how you must stand firm in the Lord, my beloved. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"I urge Euodia and  Syntyche   to agree with each other in the Lord. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Yes, and I ask you, my true yokefellow, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>I ask you, loyal Syzygus</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to help these women who have contended at my side for the gospel, along with Clement and the rest of my fellow workers, whose  names are in the Book of Life. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Rejoice in the Lord always. I will say it again: Rejoice! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Let your  gentleness be apparent to all . The Lord is near. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Be anxious for nothing, but in everything, by prayer and  petition, with thanksgiving, present your  requests to  God. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And the peace  of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your  hearts and your  minds in Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"}," Finally, brothers, whatever is true, whatever is honorable, whatever is right, whatever is pure, whatever is lovely, whatever is admirable —  if anything is excellent or  praiseworthy —  think on these things. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," Whatever you have learned or received or heard from me, or seen in me, put it into practice . And the God  of peace will be with you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Generosity of the Philippians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../2_corinthians/8.htm|>2 Corinthians 8:1–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Now I rejoice greatly in the Lord that  at last you have revived your concern for me.    You were indeed concerned, but you had no opportunity to show it. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"  I am not saying this out of need, for I have learned to be content regardless of my circumstances  . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I know  how to live humbly, and I know how to abound. In any and  every situation I have learned the secret  of being filled and being hungry,  of having plenty and having need. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I can do all things through Christ who gives me strength . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NA, SBL, NE, and WH <i>in the One who gives me strength.</i> BYZ and TR <i>in Christ who gives me strength.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Nevertheless, you have done well to share in my  affliction. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And as you Philippians  know,  in the early days of the gospel, when I left  Macedonia, no church but  you  partnered with me in the matter of giving and receiving. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"For even while I was in Thessalonica, you provided for my  needs  again and again. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Not that I am seeking a gift, but I am looking for the fruit that may be credited to your account. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," I have all I need and more, now that I have received  your gifts from Epaphroditus. They are a fragrant offering , an acceptable sacrifice, well-pleasing  to God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And my  God will supply all your needs according to His  glorious  riches in Christ Jesus. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"}," To our God and Father be glory   forever and ever. Amen. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Final Greetings"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../ephesians/6.htm#21|>Ephesians 6:21–24</a>; <a href =|../2_timothy/4.htm#19|>2 Timothy 4:19–22</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Greet all the saints in Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The brothers who are with me send you greetings . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"All the saints send you greetings ,  especially those from the household of Caesar. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your  spirit. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>Amen.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]}]}